Reasoning: The paper deals with analysis of partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) with parity objectives, which is a problem in the intersection of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), game theory (cs.GT), control systems (cs.SY), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper presents computational complexity results and memory requirements for observation-based strategies, which are relevant to all these sub-categories.
